<subSubSection id="C3646572FFD6345C71A0FE3105B34A9A" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC136F9FFD6345C71A0FE3105B34A9A" blockId="5.[151,1436,366,934]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="B90AEAEBFFD6345C71A0FE3100594AE3" bold="true" box="[198,318,405,431]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Male. This species can be separated from all others by the medial clypeal rounded; the petiole being elongate; the apical margin of the paramere being strongly concave. Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3646572FFD6345F71A0FE4603B74F1E" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="51" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC136F9FFD6345C71A0FE4605524AB0" blockId="5.[151,1436,366,934]" box="[198,1077,482,508]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="B90AEAEBFFD6345C71A0FE4600304AB0" bold="true" box="[198,343,482,508]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Description</emphasis>
. 
<typeStatus id="54C5885BFFD6345C7000FE4600B44AB0" box="[358,467,482,508]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Holotype</typeStatus>
male (
<figureCitation id="13452A7CFFD6345C7345FE46031D4AB0" box="[547,634,482,508]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="5.[151,255,1714,1738]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,991,1689]" captionTargetId="figure-356@5.[151,1436,991,1689]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 10. Habitus of Pristocera levicollis (Kieffer, 1905) comb. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5309305" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5309305/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Body length 
<quantity id="4C869B1CFFD6345C7241FE4602E44AB0" box="[807,899,482,508]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.7" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="4.7">4.7 mm</quantity>
. LFW 
<quantity id="4C869B1CFFD6345C72B2FE4605564AB0" box="[980,1073,482,508]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="3.8">3.8 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC136F9FFD6345C71A3FDAD040E4906" blockId="5.[151,1436,366,934]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Color. Head and mesosoma black except pronotal collar and posterior end of pronotal disc dark castaneous, metasoma dark castaneous, antenna, mandible, legs and veins castaneous, wings sub-hyaline.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC136F9FFD6345C71A3FDF203DD48EA" blockId="5.[151,1436,366,934]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
Head (
<figureCitation id="13452A7CFFD6345C7075FDF2000D493C" box="[275,362,598,624]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–15" captionStartId="7.[151,273,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[204,1391,184,1929]" captionTargetId="figure-40@7.[204,1391,184,1929]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 11–15. Pristocera levicollis (Kieffer, 1905) comb. nov. 11, head in dorsal view; 12, mandible; 13–15, mesosoma; 13, dorsal view; 14, lateral view; 15, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5309309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5309309/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). Mandible with five sharpened apical teeth, superior one reduced (
<figureCitation id="13452A7CFFD6345C75E3FDF205BA493C" box="[1157,1245,598,624]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–15" captionStartId="7.[151,273,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[204,1391,184,1929]" captionTargetId="figure-40@7.[204,1391,184,1929]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 11–15. Pristocera levicollis (Kieffer, 1905) comb. nov. 11, head in dorsal view; 12, mandible; 13–15, mesosoma; 13, dorsal view; 14, lateral view; 15, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5309309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5309309/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Clypeus large, with median lobe rounded, 0.5x as long as large; median carina conspicuous, high and arched in profile. Antenna short, 
<quantity id="4C869B1CFFD6345C7035FD0000D549F2" box="[339,434,676,702]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="1.7">1.7 mm</quantity>
, reaching posterior end of pronotum; scape arched, widened distad; flagellomeres short; pubescence sub-erect with some setae erect, setae long. First four antennal segments ~7:2:3:4; segment XI 1.7x as long as wide. Frons coriaceous-punctate to punctulate. Frontal groove absent. Ocellar triangle not compact, elevate, frontal angle obtuse, ocelli small. Anterior ocellus placed slightly before to imaginary line of eye top. LH 1.0x WH; WF 0.6x WH; WF 1.2x HE; OOL 0.8x WOT; DAO 0.4x WOT; posterior ocellus distant from crest of vertex 2.2x DAO. Vertex convex; corner rounded; VOL 0.7 HE. Temple almost parallel. Occipital carina present ventrally and dorsally.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF016671FFD6345C71F1F91602C54D86" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5309305" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5309305" box="[151,930,1714,1738]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5309305/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" startId="5.[151,255,1714,1738]" targetBox="[151,1436,991,1689]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="8BC136F9FFD6345C71F1F91602C54D86" blockId="5.[151,930,1714,1738]" box="[151,930,1714,1738]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
