<paragraph id="8BC136F9FFD6345F71A3F95F02BF4942" blockId="5.[151,1437,1787,2007]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1436,152,1608]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="51" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
Mesosoma (
<figureCitation id="13452A7CFFD6345C7030F95F008E4C59" box="[342,489,1787,1813]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–15" captionStartId="7.[151,273,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[204,1391,184,1929]" captionTargetId="figure-40@7.[204,1391,184,1929]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 11–15. Pristocera levicollis (Kieffer, 1905) comb. nov. 11, head in dorsal view; 12, mandible; 13–15, mesosoma; 13, dorsal view; 14, lateral view; 15, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5309309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5309309/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Figs. 13–15</figureCitation>
). Thorax dorsum shinny, punctulate, setae long. Pronotal disc trapezoidal; side slightly concave; anterior margin carinate (
<figureCitation id="13452A7CFFD6345C73F9F886039F4C70" box="[671,760,1826,1852]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–15" captionStartId="7.[151,273,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[204,1391,184,1929]" captionTargetId="figure-40@7.[204,1391,184,1929]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 11–15. Pristocera levicollis (Kieffer, 1905) comb. nov. 11, head in dorsal view; 12, mandible; 13–15, mesosoma; 13, dorsal view; 14, lateral view; 15, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5309309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5309309/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
); anterior region slightly elevate medially with rounded top. Notaulus conspicuous, incomplete anteriorly, convergent posteriorly, gradually wider posteriorly, gradually deeper posteriorly, polished inside, not reaching anterior and posterior margin of mesoscutum. Parapsidal furrow incomplete and inconspicuous anteriorly, straight, narrow, very shallow. Lateral of mesoscutum elevate without fovea anteriorly (
<figureCitation id="13452A7CFFD6345C73BEF81902534C9B" box="[728,820,1981,2007]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–15" captionStartId="7.[151,273,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[204,1391,184,1929]" captionTargetId="figure-40@7.[204,1391,184,1929]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 11–15. Pristocera levicollis (Kieffer, 1905) comb. nov. 11, head in dorsal view; 12, mandible; 13–15, mesosoma; 13, dorsal view; 14, lateral view; 15, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5309309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5309309/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Scutellar groove deep, narrow, concave, dilated laterally. Metanotum with large median elevation; median fovea sub-rectangular; metanotal groove foveolate laterally, first one very large and triangular, not punctulate inside, other ones rectangular and narrower than first one. Propodeal disc 0.8x as long as wide, anterior carina wide, disc rugulose at median anteriorly, strigulate laterally and posteriorly; spiracle bacile-shaped, slightly arched, placed completely at disc. Lateral of propodeum strigulate. Declivity of propodeum weak, convex in lateral view, imbricate and areolate dorsally. Mesopleuron with subtegular groove dilated anteriorly and uniformly narrow posteriorly, foveolate inside; episternal groove continuous to subtegular one, foveolate; mesopleural callus elevate, polished and shinning; anterior region strongly punctuate to puncticulate posteriorly, median region with large and shallow pit (
<figureCitation id="13452A7CFFD5345F71ACFE6900404AAB" box="[202,295,461,487]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–15" captionStartId="7.[151,273,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[204,1391,184,1929]" captionTargetId="figure-40@7.[204,1391,184,1929]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 11–15. Pristocera levicollis (Kieffer, 1905) comb. nov. 11, head in dorsal view; 12, mandible; 13–15, mesosoma; 13, dorsal view; 14, lateral view; 15, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5309309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5309309/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Pleurosternum with heart-shaped groove weakly defined; acetabular carina wide medially followed by large foveae (
<figureCitation id="13452A7CFFD5345F70ACFE5003464942" box="[458,545,500,526]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–15" captionStartId="7.[151,273,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[204,1391,184,1929]" captionTargetId="figure-40@7.[204,1391,184,1929]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 11–15. Pristocera levicollis (Kieffer, 1905) comb. nov. 11, head in dorsal view; 12, mandible; 13–15, mesosoma; 13, dorsal view; 14, lateral view; 15, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5309309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5309309/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Tarsal claws trifid, teeth sharpened.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC136F9FFD5345F71A3FDBE001549CE" blockId="6.[151,1436,152,1608]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Wings. Fore wing with radial vein long and slightly curved forward; metacarpus present, shorter than stigma, 0.7x as long as stigma; basal vein truncate and inclined; stigma wide and elongate. Hind wing with five apical hamuli.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC136F9FFD5345F71A0FD2A03B74F1E" blockId="6.[151,1436,152,1608]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">
Metasoma. Petiole 2x as long as wide. Gaster shinning, puncticulate to imbricate-puncticulate, setose laterally from IV tergite. Hypopygium deeply divided, densely setose apically, inner margin irregularly dentate, lateral margin with median slight concavity (
<figureCitation id="13452A7CFFD5345F7270FD78021749BA" box="[790,880,732,758]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–18" captionStartId="8.[151,270,931,955]" captionTargetBox="[166,1406,218,888]" captionTargetId="figure-403@8.[151,1436,194,908]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 16–18. Pristocera levicollis (Kieffer, 1905) comb. nov. 16, hypopigium, ventral view; 17–18, genitalia; 17, ventral view; 18, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5309311" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5309311/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). Genitalia (
<figureCitation id="13452A7CFFD5345F7562FD7805F049BA" box="[1028,1175,732,758]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–18" captionStartId="8.[151,270,931,955]" captionTargetBox="[166,1406,218,888]" captionTargetId="figure-403@8.[151,1436,194,908]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 16–18. Pristocera levicollis (Kieffer, 1905) comb. nov. 16, hypopigium, ventral view; 17–18, genitalia; 17, ventral view; 18, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5309311" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5309311/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Figs. 17–18</figureCitation>
): paramere bilaminar, placed dorsally, slightly convex, as long as basiparamere; apical margin strongly concave in lateral view, dorsal projection 1.5x as long as ventral one; ventral and dorsal margin sinuous; external surface not densely setose. Basiparamere with dorsal margin slightly concave. Basivolsella surpassing ventral margin of basiparamere, margin almost straight. Digitus large, apical margin dentate, apex sharpened and arched basad. Cuspis long, narrow, sides parallel, apex convex, base elongate and twisted dorsad and basad. Aedeagus divided into two laminae; dorsal lamina with apex divided into two pairs of apical lobes, outer lobe divided medially, lateral margin with subapical concavity, apex narrow and projected ventrad, inner lobe membranous; ventral lamina with lateral margin sinuous, apex hyaline. Genital ring wide ventrally. Basal ring absent. Apodeme extending beyond genital ring.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3646572FFD5345F71A0FBFA04034D04" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC136F9FFD5345F71A0FBFA03D14E5F" blockId="6.[151,1436,152,1608]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B90AEAEBFFD5345F71A0FBFA005F4F34" bold="true" box="[198,312,1118,1144]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species is easitly recognized as belonging to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D7AFFD5345F72F2FBFA054A4F34" box="[916,1069,1118,1144]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pristocerinae">Pristocerinae</taxonomicName>
by having the metanotum well developed medially. Within this subfamily, there are several characters, which when combined place this species in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D7AFFD5345F7072FB0800F64F89" authorityName="Klug" authorityYear="1808" box="[276,401,1196,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Pristocera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90AEAEBFFD5345F7072FB0800F64F89" box="[276,401,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Pristocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Namely, the mandibles are wide apically with five apical teeth, the genal area lacks a spine, the forewings have the subdiscoidal and the cubital veins barely visible and not reaching the apex of the wing, and the hypopygium is divided in lobes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC136F9FFD5345F71A0FA84022E4D6E" blockId="6.[151,1436,152,1608]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">
There are only five genera of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D7AFFD5345F7355FA8403AB4E76" box="[563,716,1312,1338]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pristocerinae">Pristocerinae</taxonomicName>
with the hypopygium divided into two lobes (
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D7AFFD5345F7464FA8400494E2C" authority="Stadelmann" authorityName="Stadelmann" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Dicrogenium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90AEAEBFFD5345F7464FA8404FB4E75" box="[1282,1436,1312,1337]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Dicrogenium</emphasis>
Stadelmann
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D7AFFD5345F705AFAE3030A4E2C" authority="Benoit" authorityName="Benoit" authorityYear="1957" box="[316,621,1350,1376]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Neodicrogenium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90AEAEBFFD5345F705AFAE3036B4E2C" box="[316,524,1351,1376]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Neodicrogenium</emphasis>
Benoit
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D7AFFD5345F731AFAE3022D4E2C" authority="Benoit" authorityName="Benoit" authorityYear="1957" box="[636,842,1350,1376]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Diepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90AEAEBFFD5345F731AFAE3038F4E2C" box="[636,744,1351,1376]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Diepyris</emphasis>
Benoit
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D7AFFD5345F723FFAE305204E2C" authority="Kieffer" authorityName="Kieffer. However" authorityYear="1907" box="[857,1095,1350,1376]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Kathepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90AEAEBFFD5345F723FFAE302844E2C" box="[857,995,1351,1376]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Kathepyris</emphasis>
Kieffer
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D7AFFD5345F75EEFAE3046A4E2C" authorityName="Klug" authorityYear="1808" box="[1160,1293,1351,1376]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Pristocera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90AEAEBFFD5345F75EEFAE3046A4E2C" box="[1160,1293,1351,1376]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Pristocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). However 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D7AFFD5345F71F1FAC900554ECA" authorityName="Stadelmann" authorityYear="1894" box="[151,306,1389,1414]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Dicrogenium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90AEAEBFFD5345F71F1FAC900554ECA" box="[151,306,1389,1414]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Dicrogenium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D7AFFD5345F7024FAC903604ECA" authorityName="Benoit" authorityYear="1957" box="[322,519,1389,1414]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Neodicrogenium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90AEAEBFFD5345F7024FAC903604ECA" box="[322,519,1389,1414]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Neodicrogenium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D7AFFD5345F7325FAC903CE4ECA" authorityName="Benoit" authorityYear="1957" box="[579,681,1389,1414]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Diepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90AEAEBFFD5345F7325FAC903CE4ECA" box="[579,681,1389,1414]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Diepyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are highly autapomorphic and easily recognized. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D7AFFD5345F7466FAC904FC4ECA" authorityName="Stadelmann" authorityYear="1894" box="[1280,1435,1389,1414]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Dicrogenium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90AEAEBFFD5345F7466FAC904FC4ECA" box="[1280,1435,1389,1414]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Dicrogenium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D7AFFD5345F71AFFA3000EB4EE1" authorityName="Benoit" authorityYear="1957" box="[201,396,1428,1453]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Neodicrogenium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90AEAEBFFD5345F71AFFA3000EB4EE1" box="[201,396,1428,1453]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Neodicrogenium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a large genal spine on the head, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D7AFFD5345F72DAFA3005464EE1" authorityName="Benoit" authorityYear="1957" box="[956,1057,1428,1453]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Diepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90AEAEBFFD5345F72DAFA3005464EE1" box="[956,1057,1428,1453]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Diepyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the mandible sickle-shaped with only two apical teeth. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D7AFFD5345F70BAFA1F033A4E98" authorityName="Kieffer. However" authorityYear="1907" box="[476,605,1467,1492]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Kathepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90AEAEBFFD5345F70BAFA1F033A4E98" box="[476,605,1467,1492]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Kathepyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D7AFFD5345F73FFFA1F02714E98" authorityName="Klug" authorityYear="1808" box="[665,790,1467,1492]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Pristocera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90AEAEBFFD5345F73FFFA1F02714E98" box="[665,790,1467,1492]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Pristocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are two closely related genera, but 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D7AFFD5345F75D9FA1F04274E98" authorityName="Kieffer. However" authorityYear="1907" box="[1215,1344,1467,1492]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Kathepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90AEAEBFFD5345F75D9FA1F04274E98" box="[1215,1344,1467,1492]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Kathepyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the forewings with subdiscoidal and cubital veins reaching apical margin of the wing, so that the only genus with the combination of all characters cited above is 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D7AFFD5345F73A0F9AC02264D6D" authorityName="Klug" authorityYear="1808" box="[710,833,1544,1569]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Pristocera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90AEAEBFFD5345F73A0F9AC02264D6D" box="[710,833,1544,1569]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Pristocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC136F9FFD5345F71A0F98A04034D04" blockId="6.[151,1436,152,1608]" box="[198,1380,1582,1608]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">
Given this argument, we propose a new combination of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D7AFFD5345F7231F98B052E4D04" authorityName="Kieffer. However" authorityYear="1905" box="[855,1097,1583,1608]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Pristepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="levicollis">
<emphasis id="B90AEAEBFFD5345F7231F98B052E4D04" box="[855,1097,1583,1608]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Pristepyris levicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D7AFFD5345F7516F98B043A4D04" authorityName="Azevedo &amp; Alencar" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Kieffer" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[1136,1373,1583,1608]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Pristocera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="levicollis">
<emphasis id="B90AEAEBFFD5345F7516F98B043A4D04" box="[1136,1373,1583,1608]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Pristocera levicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
